7. Backend Testing

The backend was tested using the following steps:

1. Run `Main.java`.
2. Start the Java HTTP server.
3. Log in to Admin CLI.
4. Create two users: `m1` and `m2`.
5. Create a group with ID `g1`.
6. Add both users to the group.
7. Test the users API.
8. Test the groups API.
9. Send messages from both users.
10. Retrieve messages from the group.
11. Report one message.
12. Check reported messages using option `10` in Admin CLI.

Example command for sending a message:

powershell
curl.exe -X POST "http://localhost:8080/api/messages" -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded" -d "chatId=g1&senderId=m1&content=Hello%20from%20m1"

Example command for reporting a message:

powershell
curl.exe -X POST "http://localhost:8080/api/messages/report" -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded" -d "messageId=MESSAGE_ID"


